<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-16T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-16T12:00:00-05:00" n="974" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d974">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">865.01/2216: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-16T18:00:00+01:00">March
                                        16, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 7:28 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>859. From L’Heureux. AFHQ has instructed General MacFarlane to ask
                                Badoglio for an explanation of the reasons why without prior
                                notification to the Allied Control Commission the Italian Government
                                took the initiative for exchanging representatives with the Soviets.
                                [L’Heureux.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chapin</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>